Subtitle of Senate Bill 394
TO AMEND THE LAW CONCERNING THE ALLOCATION, DISTRIBUTION, AND USE OF
REVENUES DERIVED FROM A COUNTY SALES AND USE TAXES FOR CAPITAL
IMPROVEMENTS.
______________________________________________________________________
Amendment No. 1 to Senate Bill 394
Amend Senate Bill 394 as originally introduced:
Page 2, line 11, delete "(2)(A)" and substitute "(2)(A)(i)"
AND
Page 2, line 15, delete "or a change" and substitute "or, if the requirement
of subdivision (c)(2)(A)(ii) of this section is met, a change"
AND
Page 2, delete line 17, and substitute the following:
"county.
(ii) The quorum court of a county may refer to the
vote of the people a change in the allocation or distribution of revenues
among the county and the municipalities within the county only if the
population of the largest municipality in the county exceeds the population
of the unincorporated areas of the county, according to the most recent
federal decennial census."
